data.enText: a form of a noun or verb that refers to one person or thing

data.chText: 这个动词应当用单数形式。
data.enText: The verb should be in the singular .
connected with or having the singular form

data.chText: 单数名词 / 动词 / 词尾

tr: the form of a word that is used to denote a singleton
being a single and separate person or thing
example: can the singular person be understood apart from his culture?
every fact in the world might be singular...unlike any other fact and sole of its kind"-William Jame

tr: beyond or deviating from the usual or expected
example: her speech has a funny twang
they have some funny ideas about war
the peculiar aromatic odor of cloves
something definitely queer about this town
such poise is singular in one so young

tr: grammatical number category referring to a single item or unit
composed of one member, set, or kind
the single one of its kind
example: the unique existing example of Donne's handwriting
a unique copy of an ancient manuscript
certain types of problems have unique solutions

value.def: The singular form of a word is the form that is used when referring to one person or thing.

example.ex: ...the fifteen case endings of the singular form of the Finnish noun...
example.tran: 芬兰语的名词单数形式的 15 种格尾

example.ex: The word 'you' can be singular or plural.
example.tran: 单词 you 可以是单数也可以是复数。

value.def: The singular of a noun is the form of it that is used to refer to one person or thing.

example.ex: The singular of Inuit is Inuk.
example.tran: Inuit (依努依特人)的单数形式是 Inuk。

example.ex: Barre was quickly drawn into the electoral arena, although with singular lack of success.
example.tran: 尽管胜算微乎其微，巴雷还是很快被身不由己地推到了选举的舞台上。

example.ex: It seemed a singularly ill-judged enterprise for Truman to undertake.
example.tran: 这对于杜鲁门来说似乎是一项特别不明智的事业。

example.ex: ...a former sales executive singularly unsuited for the job.
example.tran: 特别不适合这份工作的前任销售经理

value.def: If you describe someone or something as singular, you mean that they are strange or unusual.

example.ex: Cardinal Meschia was without doubt a singular character...
example.tran: 红衣主教梅斯基亚无疑是个怪人。

example.ex: Where he got that singular notion I just can't think.
example.tran: 我真想不出来他从哪来的那种奇怪念头。

example.ex: ...his abrupt, turbulent style and the singularity of his appearance.
example.tran: 他唐突、躁动的个性和怪异的外表
